embeddableConfig.description:
Counts by Status.  If a detection was found more than once in the time range for the dashboard, the detections are deduplicated for each status. For example, if a detection was found 1 time in the "NEW" state, and 6 times in the "ACTIVE" state, it will be counted once for 
"NEW" and once for "ACTIVE"

query.esql:
FROM logs-qualys_was.vulnerability* 
| KEEP qualys_was.vulnerability.unique_vuln_id, qualys_was.vulnerability.status,qualys_was.vulnerability.is_ignored | STATS count = COUNT_DISTINCT(qualys_was.vulnerability.unique_vuln_id) BY qualys_was.vulnerability.status

FROM logs-qualys_was.vulnerability* | KEEP qualys_was.vulnerability.status, qualys_was.vulnerability.id, qualys_was.vulnerability.last_test_datetime | STATS count = COUNT_DISTINCT (qualys_was.vulnerability.id) BY qualys_was.vulnerability.last_test_datetime,qualys_was.vulnerability.status
